  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Through FY2026 to date, Department of Transportation contract obligations total $8.7B across 10,665 awards with an average award size of $816K. Obligations are down 3.5% year over year. Annual obligations show a sequence of fiscal-year totals including $7B in FY21, $8B in FY22, $8.7B in FY23, $8.6B in FY24, $9B in FY25, and $8.7B in FY26. The agency’s largest NAICS spending categories in FY2026 to date include Engineering Services at $1.3B and Search, Detection, Navigation, Guidance, Aeronautical, and Nautical System and Instrument Manufacturing at $1B, followed by Telecommunications Resellers at $896M and Telephone Apparatus Manufacturing at $564M. The top vendors by obligations in FY2026 to date are HARRIS CORPORATION at $896M and RAYTHEON COMPANY at $643M, with ROHDE & SCHWARZ USA, INC. at $403M and INDRA AIR TRAFFIC, INC. at $377M also among the leaders. The data reflect current fiscal-year-to-date totals and partial-year conditions for FY2026.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How have Department of Transportation obligations moved recently?",
        "body": "Obligations are down 3.5% year over year. Fiscal-year totals show $7B in FY21, $8B in FY22, $8.7B in FY23, $8.6B in FY24, $9B in FY25, and $8.7B in FY26, indicating that FY2026 to date matches the FY23 total at $8.7B. The current-year total is a partial fiscal-year figure."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which categories and vendors account for the largest shares of spending?",
        "body": "Engineering Services accounts for $1.3B in FY2026 to date and the next largest category is Search, Detection, Navigation, Guidance, Aeronautical, and Nautical System and Instrument Manufacturing at $1B. Top vendors in FY2026 to date are HARRIS CORPORATION at $896M and RAYTHEON COMPANY at $643M, with ROHDE & SCHWARZ USA, INC. at $403M and INDRA AIR TRAFFIC, INC. at $377M also in the top ranks."
      }
    ]
  },
